{"slug": "tome", "root": "tome", "category": "book", "gloss": "a large, weighty book", "definition": "A tome is a large, weighty book — now with a connotation of ponderous learning, but originally just one volume of a longer work.", "history": "Latin *tomus*, from Greek *tomos*, 'a slice, a section of a papyrus roll,' from *temnein*, 'to cut': a tome is literally a 'cut,' one part sliced from a larger whole. The modern sense of heft is a later inflation. In fantasy the tome is the wizard's book of power; Magic uses it for card-drawing artifacts — knowledge as a resource.", "def_sources": [{"label": "Etymonline, s.v. tome", "where": "Etymology reference"}], "is_keyword": false, "etymology": {"origin": "Latin tomus ← Greek tomos ‘a slice, a roll of papyrus’, from temnein ‘to cut’", "first": "1510s", "note": "A tome is literally a ‘cut’ — one section sliced from a longer work. The weighty modern sense is a later inflation.", "hook": "Every ‘tome’ was once just one volume of many.", "lang": "Greek"}, "essay": null, "sources": ["Etymonline (Douglas Harper)", "Wiktionary", "classical lexica (Lewis & Short, LSJ, Bosworth–Toller)", "Ted's historical-magic DBs (WitchcraftStudiesDB, AgrippaDOP, MedievalMagicDB)"], "stats": {"flavor_total": 14, "oracle_total": 4, "in_flavor_cards": 14, "in_oracle_cards": 4, "name_match_count": 24, "by_variant": {"tome": 13, "tomes": 5}, "first_year": 1996, "colors": {"R": 6, "B": 4, "U": 14, "C": 13, "W": 2, "G": 1}, "by_year": {"1996": 1, "1997": 2, "2004": 2, "2006": 2, "2007": 1, "2011": 2, "2013": 1, "2015": 1, "2016": 1, "2018": 2, "2019": 2, "2020": 1, "2021": 5, "2022": 4, "2023": 3, "2024": 3, "2025": 1, "2026": 3}}, "cards": [{"id": "f515c691-07be-47ea-8bc0-46221eab8b46", "name": "Mangara's Tome", "set": "MIR", "set_name": "Mirage", "released": "1996-10-08", "type_line": "Artifact — Book", "rarity": "rare", "colors": [], "img_small": "https://cards.scryfall.io/small/front/5/5/557ebacf-4a8f-4548-a142-533b7adfdac3.jpg?1782721354", "img_